{
  "stem": "19210.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 172.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because our convoy was ambushed by the Arabic leader, Fawzi [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "El-Kauji, ?] al-Kauji-- K-A-U-J-I-- in the, in the the roads from Nahariya to, to Yehi-am.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And, and they ambushed the convoy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The-- And they killed 40, 49 members of the Haganah, my best friend, Shalom Sheineman, his brother, his sister-- no, his sister, not his brother.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He died later on.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And most of my entire unit, our, our group that always has to be together, was annihilated by Fawzi al-Kauji men.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Because the, the, the highway from Nahariyah to, to Yehi-am was zig-zag, very zig-zaggy.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The, the-- we used to call it the road of bakshish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Bakshish is an Arabic word for tip.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Because when the British build that highway, the Arabs gave them a tip to make the highway go by their gates of them, of the orange groves or, or whatever groves they had.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And so as a result, the [INAUDIBLE] for about five kilometers went like this.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So it was very, very difficult to prevent ambushes, because you couldn't see within a few hundred feet what was on the other side.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So as a result, we, we suffered.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "There was a revenge on the Transjordan army convoy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "It was the Yehi-am convoy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Yehi-am however, was a kibbutz named after a young man by the name of Yechiam Weiss.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "His father was a member of the Jewish Agency.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And Yechiam Weiss was a member of the Palmach, the Haganah commandos, that had been actually directed to blow a bridge in Achziv, A-C-H-Z-I-V, a little bit north of Nahariya.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "This was called Operation Bridges in 1947, in, in Palestine.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
